## USER RESEARCH

### Top 5 Pain Points (sourced from Corporette forums, Beautylish community threads, TikTok comment patterns, beauty forum discussions)

1. **"I want to look bold and intentional, not like I just painted my nails randomly"** — Users feel there's a gap between "work appropriate boring" and "clearly unprofessional." They want validated permission to wear dark, bold nails while looking powerful — not rebellious.

2. **"I don't know if dark nails at work makes me look sloppy or chic"** — Constant tension between wanting the dark glossy power-nail aesthetic and fear that colleagues will read it as informal. Users are actively seeking editorial backing/permission from content they trust.

3. **"I want the office siren aesthetic but I can't find nail inspo that's actually nail-focused"** — Most content talks about clothing and makeup. Nail-specific office siren content is almost non-existent. Users are searching for what the *nails specifically* look like — not the outfit.

4. **"I can't replicate the exact TikTok office siren nail — what is that dark purple-black shade?"** — Chanel Oiseau de Nuit is specifically name-dropped in the original Who What Wear viral office siren article. Users want dupes and alternatives for this now-cult shade.

5. **"Is almond shape appropriate or too fashion-forward for a corporate setting?"** — Nail shape is a genuine anxiety point. Users are navigating whether elongated shapes read as professional-chic or impractical. They need editorial guidance on the right length-to-shape ratio.

### User Sentiment
Aspirational and slightly anxious — they want to feel powerful and polished simultaneously, and they need the content to validate that the aesthetic is achievable and appropriate, not just aesthetically desirable.

